DescEn: It is often used for Nabe dish. It contains Vitamin C.

DescJa: 食べる薬、薬味といわれるのは硫化アリルが消化液の分泌を促し、ビタミンB1の吸収を助け、内臓の働きを活発にして血行を良くする働きがあるそうです。
鮮やかな緑色が特徴で茎を食べます。柔らかく、甘みがあり歯応えがよく、アスパラガスの食感とよく似ているためアスパラ菜」とも呼ばれています。

DescEn: It is a type of leaf other-veggie. It is also known as Japanese Mustard Spinach and can be stir-fried, pickled, boiled and added to soups or used fresh in salads. It is an excellent source of calcium.

DescJa: 爵薯から品種改良された馬鈴薯です。まだ誕生してから30年を超えたばかりの野菜です
ホクホクした食感がたまりません。

DescEn: The taproot of young burdock plants. It is very crisp and has a sweet and mild favor. Very popluar in macrobiotic diet which advocates its consumption. It contains a fair amount of gobō dietary fiber, calcium, potassium, amino acids, and is also low calorie.
DescJa: Macrobioticダイエット二もよく使用されるごぼう。繊維、カルシウム、アミノ酸が豊富に含まれています。
Reciep: A popular Japanese dish is kinpira gobō (約金平牛蒡), julienned or shredded burdock root and carrot, braised with soy sauce, sugar, mirin and/or sake, and sesame oil; another is burdock makizushi (約sushi filled with pickled burdock root; the burdock root is often artificially coloured orange to resemble a carrot).  It has pungent flavour with a little muddy harshness that can be reduced by soaking julienne/shredded roots in water for five to ten minutes.

DescJa: 福島県の農家だけに古くから伝わる伝統自然食品です。一滴の雫も凍る厳寒期の夜、大根を野外に吊るして凍らせ、山から吹き下ろす寒風で乾燥して出来た大根です。

DescEn: This flowering purple choy sum is a popular Chinese specialty. The young flowering shoots add a mild mustard flavor to fresh salads. Kosaitai also has an excellent flavor when lightly cooked by steaming, boiling or stir-frying.

DescJa: 福島県の農家だけに古くから伝わる伝統自然食品です。一滴の雫も凍る厳寒期の夜、もちを野外に吊るして凍らせ、山から吹き下ろす寒風で乾燥して出来た素朴な味のするおもちです。

DescEn: The flower stalk of a butterbur. known as Fuki, bog rhubarb, or giant butterbur, is an herbaceous perennial plant in the family Asteraceae. It is native to Japan, where the spring growth is relished as a other-veggie.
The traditional preparation method for this other-veggie involves pre-treating with salt and soaking in water, a technique known as itazuri, or removing harshness.

Young malukhiyah leaves are used as a green leaf other-veggie; Corchorus olitorius is used mainly in southern Asia, Egypt and Cyprus, Corchorus capsularis in Japan and China. It has a mucilaginous (約somewhat "slimy") texture, similar to okra, when cooked.

Broccoli is packed with great qualities...it contains twice the vitamin C of an orange, it has almost as much calcium as whole milk--and the calcium is better absorbed, and it contains selenium, a mineral that has been found to have anti-cancer and anti-viral properties.
Broccoli is a modest source of vitamin A and alpha-tocopherol vitamin E It also has antioxidant properties.

NameHiragana: まんがんじとうがらし

DescJa:
見て美しく、食べておいしいニューレタス。
●さまざまな葉型や赤と緑の葉色があり，見た目の美しいリーフレタス．
松丸サラダの色どりの他，花壇のふちどりや寄せ植えなどのガーデニングにも使える．
●大株にして収穫する他，ベビーサラダにも向く．
